<title type="html"><![CDATA[4/11(Thu.) 10 Benefits to Studying Abroad/15 Little White Lies Everyone Is Guilty of Telling Every Day(host: Michael)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=271&amp;p=287#p287"><![CDATA[
The first one:<br />10 Benefits to Studying Abroad | Study Abroad Guide<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.internationalstudent.com/study-abroad/guide/ten-benefits-to-studying-abroad/">https://www.internationalstudent.com/st ... ng-abroad/</a><!-- m --><br />Questions <br />1.Do you agree the benefits in the article, or is there any disadvantage of studying abroad?<br />2.Do you want to study abroad? Or do you regret you ever studied abroad? Or if you can restart your life, will you plan to study abroad?<br />3.If you want to study abroad, which country do you prefer? why?<br />4.Do you think studying in China is a good idea?<br />The second one:<br />15 Little White Lies Everyone Is Guilty of Telling Every Day<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.rd.com/advice/relationships/common-lies/">https://www.rd.com/advice/relationships/common-lies/</a><!-- m --><br />Questions:<br />1.Is telling white lies good or bad?<br />2.Have you ever told a white lie? or give examples you’ve ever heard or been told.<br />3.If you were doctor or the elder’s relative, would you tell the elder the truth when they’re diagnosed with cancer?<br />4.Will you have courage to correct club member’s mistake in speaking or writing English, or just tell a white lie (e.g. you’re great)<br /><br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00 p.m. --7:30 p.m. free talk <br />7:30 p.m. --8:10 p.m. first topic discussion <br />8:10 p.m. --8:20 p.m. Presentation <br />8:20 p.m.-- 8:40 p.m. Sharing time : articles &amp; other experiences. <br />8:40 p.m--9.:15 p.m. second topic discussion <br />9:15 p.m. -- 9:30 p.m. Presentation<br /><br />speaker time : 2 minutes for each speaker<br />host time : 3 minutes<br /><br /><br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第一區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=89">AndrewWang</a> — Thu Apr 04, 2019 10:35 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
